1. Prototyping and Iterative Design

Explanation (EN): Prototyping is a design approach where an early version of a system is built and tested. Iterative design improves the system through repeated design, testing, and refinement.
解释（中）： 原型设计是一种先构建系统早期版本并进行测试的方法。迭代设计通过反复设计、测试和改进来完善系统。
Example: Build, test, improve / 构建 → 测试 → 改进

2. Prototype

Explanation (EN): A prototype is a primitive or incomplete version of a system used to explore design ideas.
解释（中）： 原型是系统的初步或不完整版本，用于探索设计想法。
Example: Early system model / 系统初步模型

3. Types of Prototypes

Throw-Away Prototype
EN: Built, tested, then discarded; knowledge is used for the final system.
中: 一次性原型在测试后会被丢弃，设计经验用于最终系统。
Example: Paper prototype / 纸上原型
Incremental Prototype
EN: System is built and delivered in parts, adding new components each time.
中: 增量原型逐步构建系统，每次版本增加新功能。
Example: App updates / 应用程序逐步更新
Evolutionary Prototype
EN: Prototype is continuously improved and becomes the final system.
中: 演化原型不断改进，最终发展成正式系统。
Example: Beta software / 测试版软件

4. Prototype in Human–Computer Interaction (HCI)

Explanation (EN): Prototypes allow users to test and give feedback on design ideas.
解释（中）： 原型让用户参与测试并提供反馈。
Example: User testing session / 用户测试

5. Why Prototype?

Explanation (EN): Prototyping helps evaluate ideas, communicate with stakeholders, and choose better designs.
解释（中）： 原型设计有助于评估设计、与相关人员沟通并选择更好的方案。
Example: Collect feedback / 收集反馈

6. Forms of Prototypes

Hand-Drawn Prototype – Drawn by hand using paper and pencil / 使用纸和笔手绘界面
Example: Paper sketches / 手绘草图
Tool-Drawn Prototype – Designed using software tools / 使用软件工具设计界面
Example: Drawn in computer / 电脑绘制界面
Screen Prototype – Shown on screen with little or no function / 功能很少或没有
Example: Click does nothing / 点击无反应
Functional Prototype – Some buttons and menus work / 部分功能可运行
Example: Working buttons / 可运行按钮

7. What Designers Need to Know

Explanation (EN): Prototypes help explore technical issues, workflow, and screen layout.
解释（中）： 原型有助于探索技术问题、工作流程和界面布局。
Example: Icon size / 图标大小

8. Low-Fidelity Prototypes (Low-Fi Prototypes)

Explanation (EN): Simple, cheap, and easy to change, often made of paper.
解释（中）： 低保真原型简单、便宜、容易修改，通常使用纸张制作。
Example: Paper mock-up / 纸质模型

9. Types of Low-Fidelity Prototypes

Sketching – Quick drawings for ideas / 快速构思绘图
Example: Rough drawing / 粗略草图
Storyboard – Sequence of sketches showing tasks / 展示任务流程
Example: Step-by-step screens / 操作步骤画面
Wireframe – Shows layout and navigation / 展示布局和导航
Example: Page layout / 页面布局
Card-Based Prototyping – Uses cards to represent screens / 用卡片代表界面
Example: Website pages / 网站页面
Wizard of Oz Prototype – Human secretly controls system / 人在幕后模拟功能
Example: Fake voice assistant / 模拟语音助手

10. High-Fidelity Prototypes (High-Fi Prototypes)

Explanation (EN): Closely resemble the final system in appearance.
解释（中）： 高保真原型在外观上非常接近最终系统。
Example: App mock-up / 应用界面模型

11. Tools for High-Fidelity Prototyping

Explanation (EN): Software tools are used to create realistic prototypes.
解释（中）： 使用软件工具制作逼真的原型。
Example: Adobe XD, Figma / Adobe XD、Figma

12. Prototype Compromises

Explanation (EN): Prototypes involve compromises between detail and functionality.
解释（中）： 原型需要在细节和功能之间取舍。
Horizontal Prototype – Many functions, little detail / 功能多但细节少
Example: Many menus / 多菜单界面
Vertical Prototype – Few functions, high detail / 功能少但细节多
Example: One detailed feature / 一个详细功能

13. Workplace Design and Ergonomics

Explanation (EN): Focuses on comfort and safety.
解释（中）： 人体工学关注舒适和安全。
Example: Comfortable chair / 舒适的椅子

14. Importance of Workplace Layout

Explanation (EN): Good layout improves productivity and reduces strain.
解释（中）： 良好的布局提高效率并减少身体负担。
Example: Open office / 开放式办公室

15. Environmental Factors in Workplace Design

Explanation (EN): Environmental factors affect performance and comfort.
解释（中）： 环境因素影响用户表现和舒适度。
Lighting: Proper lighting / 合适的照明
Noise Level: Quiet office / 安静的办公室
Temperature and Air Quality: Good ventilation / 良好通风
